This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. From Obinna Odogwu, Awka Chief Judge of Anambra State, Justice Onochie Anyachebelu, on Thursday morning, administered the oath of office on Prof. Chukwuma Soludo as the new governor of the state. Soludo, former Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) governor, won the November 6, 2021 governorship election on the platform of the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA). He took the oath of office at about 9:50am. Before he was sworn in, his deputy, Dr Onyeka Ibezim, took his oath of office.